{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id5b56a96f-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s1814"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1814"},"text":"§ 1814.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Transfer or assignment; expiration; renewal","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id5b56a970-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s1814/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Transfer or assignment prohibited","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A certificate of registration may not be transferred or assigned.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id5b56a971-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s1814/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Expiration; renewals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id5b56a972-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s1814/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Unless earlier suspended or revoked, a certificate shall expire twelve months from the date of issuance, except that (A) certificates issued under this chapter during the period beginning ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-12-01"},"text":"December 1, 1982","children":[],"tail":", and ending "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-11-30"},"text":"November 30, 1983","children":[],"tail":", may be issued for a period of up to twenty-four months for the purpose of an orderly transition to registration under this chapter, (B) a certificate may be temporarily extended by the filing of an application with the Secretary at least thirty days prior to its expiration date, and (C) the Secretary may renew a certificate for additional twelve-month periods or for periods in excess of twelve months but not in excess of twenty-four months."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id5b56a973-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s1814/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Eligibility for renewals for periods of more than twelve months shall be limited to farm labor contractors who have not been cited for a violation of this chapter, or any regulation under this chapter, or the Farm Labor Contractor Registration Act of 1963 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2041"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2041","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], or any regulation under such Act, during the preceding five years."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id5b56a974-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/470/tI/s104"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–470, title I, § 104","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-01-14"},"text":"Jan. 14, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/2589"},"text":"96 Stat. 2589","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id5b56a975-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id5b56a976-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id5b56a977-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Farm Labor Contractor Registration Act of 1963, referred to in subsec. (b)(2), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/582"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–582","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-09-07"},"text":"Sept. 7, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/920"},"text":"78 Stat. 920","children":[],"tail":", which was classified generally to chapter 52 (§ 2041 et seq.) of Title 7, Agriculture, and was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/470/tV/s523"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–470, title V, § 523","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-01-14"},"text":"Jan. 14, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/2600"},"text":"96 Stat. 2600","children":[],"tail":". See section 1801 et seq. of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id5b56a978-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"id5b56a979-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective 90 days from ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-01-14"},"text":"Jan. 14, 1983","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/470/s524"},"text":"section 524 of Pub. L. 97–470","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s1801"},"text":"section 1801 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
